A system of four objects for the living room. Not conceived individually but as parts of a whole, and the whole is called *ah ok* because that's what you say when something works without needing an explanation.

<h2>The brief</h2>

The starting point was the concept of Orografie: reinterpreting the fundamental amphibious concept in furniture design, with a reference to Mediterranean culture. The brief asked to move beyond traditional typological categorisations. To design new functions before new forms.

The theoretical reference was twofold: on one side the morphological and typological analysis of Salvatore Greco, and on the other the need to recover the critical and radical capacity of Italian design as described by Vincenzo Castellana.

