<h2>The concept</h2>

The process began with a deconstruction of the letters that make up "ah, ok". Each letter became the generative principle of an object: lines and circles as a fundamental modular unit, progressively transformed into functional forms through sketches and iterations.

Form does not come first. Form follows function and function follows the observation of how people use spaces, often in ways that were never anticipated.

