<h2>The process</h2>

The initial moodboard sought to communicate lightness and fluidity: the concept of a domestic space that adapts to its inhabitants rather than the other way around. The selected images emphasised modularity, the versatility of postures, the possibility of reconfiguring a space without effort.

From there the process moved through sketches, deconstruction of the letters, simplification of forms into lines and circles, and a series of iterations that led to the final forms. Each object went through many versions before arriving at the one published here.

The system was also developed at a typographic level: an original typeface called *ahok Bold*, built on the same modular forms as the objects, adapts the project's geometries to the graphic plane.

The project was co-developed with Sofia Foster and Stefania Rapisarda.